To preapre your environment

Make sure that the JDK is installed on your system. You can download the latest JDK from the official Oracle website: https://www.oracle.com/java/technologies/downloads/

Once you have installed the JDK, set the JAVA_HOME environment variable to the installation directory of the JDK. For example, if you have installed the JDK in C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_281, set JAVA_HOME to that path.

Add the bin directory of the JDK to the PATH environment variable. For example, if you have installed the JDK in C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_281, add C:\Program Files\Java\jdk1.8.0_281\bin to the PATH variable.

Open a new command prompt window and try running the javac command again.



To run this program:

Save the code in a file named Main.java
Compile the code by running javac Main.java  -> this will create 3 classes in your working dir
Run the program by running java Main

To compile all java files in dir  
javac *.java